article.linkText: Kansas upsets Arizona to reach Final Four
article.story: TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- Andre Iguodala scored 23 points to lead No. 4 Arizona to a 116-91 victory over Team Nike in an exhibition game Thursday night. Iguodala had 12 points as the Wildcats took a 58-48 halftime lead, but he really put on a show in the second half. With Arizona leading 77-60, the sophomore had a give-n-go dunk, a slam off a lob pass from freshman Mustafa Shakur and then another rim-rattler after an around-the-back assist from Chris Rodgers to make it 86-62 with almost 11 minutes left in the game. Channing Frye had 20 points for Arizona, while Shakur added 19, Hassan Adams 18, Rodgers 15 and Salim Stoudamire 12. Wayland White had 17 points for Team Nike, while Jeff Boschee had 16 and Charles Wills added 13.
